<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B11FFDDF78EF813F61BF9F3" pageId="15" pageNumber="526" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="D126FA521B11FFDDF78EF813F6A0FAB7" blockId="15.[2073,2666,1122,1545]" pageId="15" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis id="E3ED26401B11FFDDF78EF813F725FBA3" bold="true" box="[2074,2229,1122,1151]" pageId="15" pageNumber="526">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B11FFDDF759F813F7CEFB7A" authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1903" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="526" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sericeus">Ctenomys sericeus |. A. Allen, 1903</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="61F1F00F1B11FFDDF7ECF8F4F6A0FAB7" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798388319" pageId="15" pageNumber="526">“Cordilleras, upper Rio Chico de Santa Cruz, Patagonia.” Restricted by U. FJ. Pardinas in 2013 to “confluencia de los rios Belgrano y Chico (~48°26&quot; S, 71°20” W), departamento Rio Chico, Santa Cruz, Argentina.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D126FA521B11FFDDF78EF903F61BF9F3" blockId="15.[2073,2666,1122,1545]" lastBlockId="15.[1458,2665,1550,2291]" pageId="15" pageNumber="526">
Based on biogeography, C. 
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B11FFDDF600F903F662FA4F" authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1903" box="[2452,2546,1394,1427]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="526" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sericeus">sericeus</taxonomicName>
was classified in the Patagonian group but based on molecular markers in the magellanicusspecies group. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 28-30, and sperm form is simple asymmetric. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B11FFDDFA21FA44F682F98A" box="[1461,2322,1589,1622]" pageId="15" pageNumber="526" type="distribution">
